name: Zucchini Roll-Ups
author: Raelynne-Tim Murphy
ingredients: 2 small zucchini, cut lengthwise into slightly less than 1/4-inch slices
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Place zucchini directly on oven rack near the bottom
Cook until slightly softened, 5 to 10 minutes
Place bacon slices on paper towels
Heat in microwave on High until cooked but not crisp, about 3 minutes
Place a layer of bacon on each zucchini slice; top with a slice of fontina cheese
Tightly roll each layered zucchini strip and secure with a toothpick or skewer
Bake zucchini rolls in the preheated oven until cheese is melted, about 10 minutes
